teeming with life.</i>

1402
01:48:38,800 --> 01:48:42,079
<i>But then the continent
started to drift south...</i>

1403
01:48:42,080 --> 01:48:44,242
<i>...and by the time it
was done drifting...</i>

1404
01:48:44,243 --> 01:48:49,770
<i>...the dense forests had all been
replaced with a new ground cover: ice.</i>

1405
01:48:52,560 --> 01:48:57,327
<i>As for the former inhabitants, they'd
all died or moved on long ago.</i>

1406
01:48:57,320 --> 01:49:00,961
<i>Well, almost all of them.</i>

1407
01:49:03,040 --> 01:49:06,119
<i>The emperor penguin is
technically a bird...</i>

1408
01:49:06,120 --> 01:49:09,919
<i>...although one that makes
his home in the sea.</i>

1409
01:49:09,920 --> 01:49:12,879
<i>So if you're wondering what he's
doing up here on the ice...</i>

1410
01:49:12,880 --> 01:49:16,079
<i>...well, that's
part of our story.</i>

1411
01:49:16,080 --> 01:49:18,447
<i>Each year at around
the same time...</i>

1412
01:49:18,440 --> 01:49:20,841
<i>...he will leave the comfort
of his ocean home...</i>

1413
01:49:20,842 --> 01:49:23,319
<i>...and embark on a
remarkable journey.</i>

1414
01:49:23,320 --> 01:49:25,919
<i>He will travel a great distance.</i>

1415
01:49:25,920 --> 01:49:28,969
<i>And though he is a
bird, he won't fly.</i>

1416
01:49:28,960 --> 01:49:32,521
<i>Though he lives in the
sea, he won't swim.</i>

